description:
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting Healthcare Assistantsto be part of a newservice to provideEnd of Life care to patients in the South Tyneside and surrounding areas. The service will be an overnight shift pattern coordinated from our Marie Curie Hospice in Newcastle. Working hours will cover 10:00pm to 07:00am&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Caring for dying patients can be challenging and is not a job for just anybody. We are currently recruiting to the role of Health Care Assistant working across the South Tyneside and surrounding areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have experience of End of Life care and be ready and able to make a real difference. Our service is a one-to-one approach to care, so you&#39;re sure to enjoy plenty of meaningful contact with patients and their families in their own homes. Working without close supervision, you&#39;ll have the opportunity to use your own initiative in line with the patient&#39;s established care plans. You&#39;ll be required to carry out a range of duties including monitoring symptoms, helping to assist with medications and personal care and keeping detailed records. You&#39;ll also help patients to meet their dietary needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To join our dedicated, caring team, you&#39;ll need an S/NVQ Level 2/3 qualification or an equivalent certificate/diploma and relevant experience within a care setting. Emotional strength and the ability to work on your own are crucial, though we will of course provide excellent on-going training and support. We expect you to have a talent for forging strong empathetic relationships with all kinds of people and have a professional approach with all members of the Multi Disciplinary Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due to the nature of the role a flexible approach with access and use of a car with business insurance is essential.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want compassionate and caring individuals who can demonstrate empathy and understanding. You will treat every patient and family member you meet with the upmost respect as an individual and display person centred care by listening to what is important to them in their last weeks or days of life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marie Curie values its staff and recognises that caring for dying patients can be challenging at times. We provide excellent on-going training as well as clinical supervision and 121 support from your line manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I&lt;/strong&gt;f you would like more information on this role please contactLynn Beston, Clinical Nurse Manager, lynn.beston@mariecurie.org.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Every day of your life matters - from the first to the last. When you work for Marie Curie, you understand that better than ever. We&#39;re a passionate, committed and diverse team of more than 4,400 staff and 12,000 volunteers, here for people living with any terminal illness, and their families. We offer expert care, guidance and support, to help them get the most from the time they have left.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marie Curie is committed to its values, which underpin our work. We take stringent steps to ensure that the people who join our organisation through employment or volunteering, are suitable for their roles and are committed to safeguarding all our people from harm. This includes our staff, volunteers and all those who use or come into contact with our services. We are dedicated to creating not just a safe place to work but also a supportive and rewarding one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marie Curie is committed to a world where everyone can thrive and fulfil their potential. We are devoted to the social justice imperatives and organisational benefits of full diversity, inclusion and equity in the workplace, and are a Stonewall champion. We actively encourage and welcome applications from candidates of diverse cultures, perspectives and lived experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be subject to receiving a satisfactory enhanced criminal record check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We reserve the right to close this vacancy early. Agencies need not apply.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
